A 'Libellula depressa', also known as the broad-bodied chaser, is a species of dragonfly. 
It has a stout body and broad wings, with a wingspan of about 7.5 centimeters. 
The male has a blue-grey coloration with a dark abdomen and blue eyes, while the female has a brown-yellow coloration with a yellow abdomen and brown eyes. 
The wings are clear with brown patches at the base. 
This dragonfly is commonly found near slow-moving water sources such as ponds and marshes, as well as in meadows and woodland edges. 
It is active from April to September and feeds on other insects, including mosquitoes and flies. 
The 'Libellula depressa' is a popular subject for photography and scientific study due to its striking appearance and behavior.
